message.content:
Eggnog is a traditional holiday beverage enjoyed in many cultures around the world. 
It is typically made with milk, eggs, sugar, spices, and sometimes alcohol. 
The drink has a creamy and frothy texture, with a pale yellow to light beige color. 
It is often garnished with a sprinkle of nutmeg on top. 
Eggnog can be served hot or cold and is commonly found at holiday parties and festivities. 
It is considered a classic and indulgent treat that is enjoyed by many during the winter season. 
Overall, eggnog is a rich and comforting beverage that is enjoyed by many people during the holiday season.
